<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="25" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10624/8.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of the United
                                    States</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Emperor of
                                    Austria</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-01"><hi rend="italic">December 1,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In the fullness of honored years Your Majesty completes the sixtieth year
                            of sovereignty over a great nation. I offer you most cordial
                            felicitations upon this memorable occasion, with earnest wishes for your
                            welfare and for the prosperity of the peoples whose destinies you guide.
                            I shall attend the celebration of this event which is to be held in this
                            city.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>